app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:336:## CRITICAL RULES - DO NOT INFER
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:337:- DO NOT infer experience without EXPLICIT evidence in the CV
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:338:- If the candidate worked at a tech company, DO NOT assume they know programming
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:339:- If the candidate is a "Project Manager", DO NOT assume Agile/Scrum experience
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:340:- Each competency must have DIRECT, EXPLICIT evidence in the CV to be rated "meets" or "exceeds"
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:341:- When in doubt between two levels, ALWAYS choose the LOWER level
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:342:- If your analysis uses words like "probably", "suggests", "may have", "indicates" - classify as INFERRED evidence
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:345:- EXCEEDS (100 pts): Exceptional evidence with measurable results. Experience >50% above requirement. MUST have explicit, quantified evidence.
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:346:- MEETS (75 pts): Clearly and directly demonstrates the competency/experience. Specific examples present.
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:347:- PARTIAL (40 pts): Related but indirect evidence, or experience below requirement. May be implicit.
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:348:- MISSING (0 pts): No evidence found in the CV. Do NOT guess or assume.
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:351:- EXPLICIT: Direct statement in CV (e.g., "5 years of Python", "Led team of 8")
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:352:- IMPLICIT: Reasonably derived from context (e.g., "Senior Developer at Google" implies coding skills)
app/domains/cv_screening/services/rubric_evaluation_service.py:353:- INFERRED: Weak connection, assumption-based (e.g., "worked in tech" → "may know Python")
